INSERT INTO `Directions` (RecipeID, SortOrder, Direction) VALUES ('7743', '5', 'Light a grill or heat 2 grill pans. Lightly brush the tuna steaks with oil and season with salt and pepper. Grill the steaks over moderately high heat, turning once, until medium rare, about 6 minutes.'),
('7743', '6', 'Transfer the steaks to plates, spoon the sauce on top and serve with the wasabi on the side.'),
('7747', '1', 'Rinse the beans and pick over for small stones or debris. Soak the beans in cold water overnight with a 2-inch piece of kombu.Discard the soaking liquid, and place the beans and the other ingredients for cooking them in a 6-quart pot.'),
('7747', '2', 'Add enough cold water to fill the pot half full. Bring to a boil. Simmer 1 to 1  hours, until the beans are tender. Turn off the heat, add the tablespoon of kosher salt and allow to cool in the cooking liquid.'),
('7747', '3', 'Drain and discard the cooking liquid, onion, celery and kombu.'),
('7747', '4', 'Whisk the dressing ingredients in a small bowl until emulsified.To make the salad, transfer the cooked beans to a serving bowl.'),
('7747', '5', 'Add the celery, sliced shallot, fresh mint and (optional tuna.)'),
('7747', '6', 'Pour the dressing over the beans and toss to blend.'),
('7747', '7', 'Serve at room temperature.'),
('7753', '1', 'In a medium bowl, mix the tuna with the onion, olive oil, vinegar, basil and crushed red pepper. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7753', '2', 'Heat a panini press or griddle.'),
('7753', '3', 'Spread the cut sides of the rolls with mustard and mayonnaise and top each roll half with a slice of cheese.'),
('7753', '4', 'Spread the tuna salad on the bottoms and cover with the pickles. Close the sandwiches and spread the outsides of the rolls with the butter.'),
('7753', '5', 'Add the sandwiches to the press and cook over moderate heat until the cheese is melted, about 6 minutes.'),
('7753', '6', 'Cut the sandwiches in half and serve.'),
('7754', '1', 'Combine first 11 ingredients in a bowl. stir well. Cover and chill.'),
('7754', '2', 'Arrange fish slices on 4 chilled appetizer plates. Spoon chilled Key lime mixture over fish, and drizzle with a few drops of sesame oil and soy sauce.'),
('7754', '3', 'Serve immediately.'),
('7755', '1', 'Whisk first 9 ingredients in large bowl. Stir in onion.'),
('7755', '2', 'Transfer mixture to resealable plastic bag.'),
('7755', '3', 'Add tuna and seal bag, releasing any excess air. turn to coat.'),
('7755', '4', 'Let marinate at room temperature 1 hour, turning occasionally. (Alternatively, chill 4 hours, turning occasionally, then allow to return to room temperature before continuing.)'),
('7756', '1', 'With a sharp knife, cut the tuna into 4 large pieces for appetizer portion, 2 large pieces for dinner portion.  Use your judgment on what shape you want to cut your tuna because not all tuna is the same size or shape.  However, the shape should somewhat resemble a miniature brick.'),
('7756', '2', 'Season the tuna pieces with salt and pepper. Coat lightly on all sides with bread crumbs.'),
('7756', '3', 'Heat olive oil in a large heavy skillet over high heat. The pan should be as hot as you can get it.'),
('7756', '4', 'Place the tuna in the pan, and sear on each side for about 45 seconds for small portions, or 1 minute for large.'),
('7756', '5', 'Remove from pan. The tuna will be very rare.'),
('7756', '6', 'Slice each ''brick'' into 1/4 inch thick slices, and fan out on a serving plate. Enjoy plain, or with the condiments of your choice.'),
('7761', '1', 'Cut the tuna into long, fat, squared-off strips or "logs" 1 to 1-1/2 inches thick. Coat the tuna with the oil and season lightly with salt and pepper. Set a 10-inch heavy-duty skillet over high heat. When the pan is very hot, after 2 to 3 minutes, sear the tuna logs for 20 to 30 seconds on each side-they should be seared outside and rare inside.'),
('7761', '2', 'Transfer to a clean cutting board and slice 1/4 inch thick.    In a -medium bowl, combine the pineapple, scallions, lime juice, soy sauce, and ginger.'),
('7761', '3', 'Add the avocado and gently stir to combine. Stir in the chopped cilantro.    To assemble, set the tuna slices on rice crackers. top each with a small spoonful of the salsa and a whole cilantro leaf. You may have extra crackers and salsa.'),
('7764', '1', 'Cut tuna in half lengthwise.'),
('7764', '2', 'Combine spices in a small bowl. Season tuna all over with spices and put in a 4- by 8-in. loaf pan. Chill, covered, 3 to 5 hours.'),
('7764', '3', 'Preheat oven to 30'),
('7764', '4', 'Add bay leaf, herb sprigs, garlic, and zest to tuna, tucking them around fish. pour in enough oil to cover by 1/4 in.'),
('7764', '5', 'Bake tuna 25 minutes, uncovered, lowering heat if necessary to keep oil from boiling.'),
('7764', '6', 'Let tuna cool to room temperature in oil.'),
('7764', '7', 'Lift one piece of tuna from oil. separate into thick flakes. Top baguette slices with tuna, using more if needed, and arrange on a platter with olives and radishes. Scatter minced parsley over platter.'),
('7764', '8', 'Drizzle tuna with some of the oil, and flick some oil onto the olives and radishes too.'),
('7764', '9', 'Make ahead: Through step 3, up to 10 days, chilled. Bring to room temperature before serving.'),
('7765', '1', 'Season tuna with kosher salt and fresh cracked pepper.'),
('7765', '2', 'Place arugula and capers on a plate.'),
('7765', '3', 'Combine oil and lemon juice, salt and pepper.'),
('7765', '4', 'Heat your grill to high heat and clean grate well. When grill is hot, spray grate with oil to prevent sticking then place tuna on the grill. cook one minute without moving. Turn over and cook an additional minute. remove from heat and set aside on a plate.Slice tuna on the diagonal and place on top of salad. Top with lemon vinaigrette and eat immediately.Print This3 SP 8 PP Fish Recipes Grilled Recipes Recipes Salad Seafood Recipes Spring Summerposted June 28, 2011 by Gina15 Comments'),
('7766', '1', 'In a food processor, combine chick peas, garlic, parsley, sesame seeds and red pepper flakes, and pulse until coarsely chopped and combined.'),
('7766', '2', 'Remove to a bowl, stir in extra-virgin olive oil, and add lemon juice.'),
('7766', '3', 'Heat canola oil in a saute pan and season tuna with salt, pepper, and paprika. Sear both sides and remove to a utility platter to let rest.'),
('7766', '4', 'While tuna is resting, arrange bread slices on baking sheet and toast in oven.'),
('7766', '5', 'Slice tuna and assemble appetizers by spooning hummus on each toast round and then topping with a piece of tuna. Top tuna with another small amount of hummus, about 1/8 teaspoon, and a small sprig of parsley.'),
('7768', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Meanwhile, in a food processor, pulse bread and 1 teaspoon oil until coarse crumbs form.'),
('7768', '2', 'Spread on a rimmed baking sheet. season with salt and pepper.'),
('7768', '3', 'Bake until golden, tossing occasionally, 6 to 8 minutes.'),
('7774', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350 degrees'),
('7774', '2', 'In a large bowl, stir together first six ingredients until well combined.'),
('7774', '3', 'Spread into a small greased casserole dish then sprinkle bread crumbs and parmesan cheese evenly over the top.'),
('7774', '4', 'Bake uncovered in a preheated 350 degree oven for 30 minutes and serve warm.'),
('7776', '1', 'Combine the garlic, chickpeas, tuna with its oil, sun-dried tomatoes, olives, and vinegar in the bowl of a food processor. Pulse 5 to 10 times, scraping the bowl down every few times, until you have a very coarse and chunky paste. (If you pulse it too much, it gets unappealingly mushy and pasty. Not what you want.)'),
('7776', '2', 'Transfer the spread to a mixing bowl, stir in the parsley and give it a taste. Season with salt and pepper, stirring in just enough olive oil to bring it together.'),
('7776', '3', 'Serve the spread with flatbread, scoop it onto a sandwich, or stuff it into whole jarred piquillo peppers for an impressive but easy appetizer.'),
('7777', '1', 'Mix first 4 ingredients until well blended.  Stir in 1 Tbsp. basil.'),
('7777', '2', 'Mix 2 Tbsp. dressing mixture with remaining basil, tomatoes, onions and cheese. set aside.'),
('7777', '3', 'Pour remaining dressing mixture over tuna in shallow dish. turn to coat both sides.  Cover. refrigerate 30 min. to 1 hour to marinate.'),
('7777', '4', 'Heat greased grill to medium-high heat.'),
('7777', '5', 'Remove tuna from marinade. discard marinade.  Grill tuna 5 to 7 min. on each side or until tuna flakes easily with fork.'),
('7777', '6', 'Serve topped with tomato mixture.'),
('7778', '1', '1 In a saucepan, add 1 cup of elbow macaroni to 1 quart of boiling water with an added teaspoon of salt. Cook at a rolling boiluncovered for about 10 minutes until the macaroni is just a little more cooked than al dente. When ready, remove from heat, drain and rinse with cold water.2 While the macaroni is cooking, assemble the other ingredients. In a large bowl mix the green onion, bell peppers, parsley, tuna, celery and lemon.'),
('7778', '2', 'Add the cooked and drained macaroni. Fold in the mayonnaise until well mixed.'),
('7778', '3', 'Add the paprika.'),
('7778', '4', 'Add fresh ground pepper to taste.At this point you can make ahead and chill.3When ready to serve, gently fold in the lettuce.The salad does not make good leftovers as the lettuce will eventually get soggy.'),
('7779', '1', 'In a medium bowl, pour 3/4 cup boiling water over the tamarind pods and set aside to soak.'),
('7779', '2', 'Combine the peppercorns, coriander seeds and cumin seeds in a spice grinder and grind until quite fine.'),
('7779', '3', 'Add the ground almonds and grind again briefly.'),
('7779', '4', 'Add the turmeric to the spice mixture and set aside.'),
('7779', '5', 'Using a potato masher or the back of a wooden spoon, crush the (now soft) tamarind pods to release the pulp, stirring to combine with the water, which will turn cloudy and sort of pinkish-brown. Strain the liquid through a fine mesh sieve into a small bowl and discard the pods. Set aside.'),
('7779', '6', 'Heat the oil in a large, wide saut pan over medium heat, add the onion, garlic, ginger and a large pinch of salt and cook gently for about 5 minutes, until starting to soften. Stir in the spices and cook for another couple of minutes, until quite fragrant.'),
('7779', '7', 'Add the coconut milk, chiles, 2/3 cup of the tamarind water, and the lime juice and simmer for about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Salt the tuna pieces lightly and add them to the pan, reducing the heat to low. Simmer until the tuna is just cooked through, 4 to 5 minutes, turning the pieces once halfway through so they cook evenly. Taste and add more salt if needed, and garnish with the cilantro.'),
('7779', '8', 'Serve with rice.'),
('7782', '1', 'Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring well to coat.'),
('7782', '2', 'Place 4 bread slices on a flat surface. top each bread slice with 1 cheese slice. Divide tuna mixture evenly among bread slices. top each serving with 1 remaining bread slice.'),
('7782', '3', 'Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Lightly coat sandwiches with cooking spray.'),
('7782', '4', 'Place sandwiches in pan. top with another heavy skillet. Cook 3 minutes on each side or until lightly browned (leave skillet on sandwiches as they cook).'),
('7783', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk the lemon juice with the mustard, then slowly whisk in the olive oil. Stir in the chives and season the lemon-mustard vinaigrette with salt and pepper.'),
('7783', '2', 'In a large bowl, gently toss the drained tuna with the sliced celery, butter beans and capers.'),
('7783', '3', 'Add the lemon-mustard vinaigrette and toss to coat the salad. Season the salad with salt and pepper and serve at once.'),
('7785', '1', 'Preheat an oven to 450F. Prepare a hot fire in a grill.'),
('7785', '2', 'Place the tomatoes on a baking sheet and toss with 1 Tbs. of the olive oil. Arrange them, cut sides up, on the sheet and season with salt. Roast until tender, about 20 minutes.'),
('7785', '3', 'Let cool, then cut in half crosswise.Meanwhile, bring a large pot three-fourths full of salted water to a boil over high heat.'),
('7785', '4', 'Add the pasta and cook until al dente (tender but firm to the bite), about 10 minutes.'),
('7785', '5', 'Drain, rinse under cold running water and drain again. Set aside.'),
('7785', '6', 'Brush both sides of the tuna fillets with 1 Tbs. of the oil. Season well with salt and pepper.'),
('7785', '7', 'Place on the grill rack 4 to 6 inches above the fire and grill until lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Turn and cook for 3 to 4 minutes more for medium, or until done to your liking.'),
('7785', '8', 'Transfer to a cutting board, let cool and cut into 3/4-inch cubes.In a food processor or blender, combine the basil leaves and the remaining 1/2 cup oil. Pulse or blend until chopped to a coarse puree.'),
('7785', '9', 'Add the vinegar and season with salt and pepper. Pulse or blend until combined.In a large bowl, combine the pasta, tomatoes and any accumulated juices, tuna, mozzarella, parsley and the basil dressing. Toss gently and serve.'),
('7785', '10', 'Serves 8.Adapted from Williams-Sonoma Outdoors Series, Beach House Cooking, by Charles Pierce (Time-Life Books, 1999).'),
('7786', '1', 'Combine tuna and next 7 ingredients in a bowl. toss gently. Cover and chill until ready to serve.'),
('7786', '2', 'Spoon Avocado Salsa evenly into 6 martini glasses. Top each evenly with tuna mixture. drizzle each with 2 tablespoons Kaffir Lime Syrup.'),
('7786', '3', 'Garnish, if desired.'),
('7789', '1', 'Place cracked wheat in a bowl and cover with boiling water. Allow to stand for 1012 minutes or until tender.'),
('7789', '2', 'Drain well, squeezing out any excess water.'),
('7789', '3', 'Place in a bowl, add tuna and mix to combine.In a separate bowl combine the cucumber, tomato, olives, basil, salt and pepper and toss to mix. To serve, and drizzle the salad with olive oil and vinegar. You could also serve this with lemon wedges and mint leaves.'),
('7789', '4', 'Serves 2.'),
('7794', '1', 'Heat a medium nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Sprinkle tuna with salt and pepper.'),
('7794', '2', 'Add tuna to pan. cook 1 minute on each side or until desired degree of doneness.'),
('7794', '3', 'Cut tuna into 8 strips and cool.'),
('7794', '4', 'Shape 1/4 cup rice into a rectangle about the size of 1 tuna strip.'),
('7794', '5', 'Place 1 tuna strip across middle joints of fingers, palm side up.'),
('7794', '6', 'Spread 1/8 teaspoon wasabi over tuna strip. top with shaped rice. Close hand and gently press rice and tuna together.'),
('7794', '7', 'Wrap 1 nori strip around center of nigiri, ending underneath rice. Repeat with remaining ingredients.'),
('7795', '1', 'Place shallot, bay leaf and wine in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce until the wine is almost evaporated, about 5 minutes.'),
('7795', '2', 'Remove from the heat, discard bay leaf and transfer to a small bowl.'),
('7795', '3', 'Add sour cream, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon dill, mustard and 1/4 teaspoon salt. stir to combine.Put breadcrumbs, pistachios, the remaining 1 teaspoon dill and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a blender or food processor. Process until finely ground.'),
('7795', '4', 'Transfer to a shallow bowl. Dredge both sides of the tuna in the pistachio mixture.'),
('7795', '5', 'Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat.'),
('7795', '6', 'Add the tuna and cook until browned, adjusting the heat as necessary to prevent burning, 4 to 5 minutes per side for medium-rare.'),
('7795', '7', 'Serve with the lemon-dill sauce.'),
('7799', '1', 'Combine first 8 ingredients. refrigerate until ready to serve.'),
('7799', '2', 'Brush fish with A.'),
('7799', '3', 'Heat oil in large skillet on high heat.'),
('7799', '4', 'Add fish. cook 3 min. or until edges are white but centers are still pink, turning after 2 min.'),
('7799', '5', 'Serve with bean salad.'),
('7800', '1', 'Drain pasta and add to sauce. stir to combine.'),
('7800', '2', 'Transfer to a large serving platter and serve immediately with freshly grated cheese.'),
('7801', '1', 'Prepare a grill for medium heat (350 to 450). In a small bowl, combine honey and mustard. Rub tuna with mixture and let marinate at room temperature, 10 minutes.'),
('7801', '2', 'Use an oil-soaked paper towel to wipe grill grates. Cook tuna just until grill marks appear, 1 to 2 minutes on each side, leaving tuna rare inside.'),
('7801', '3', 'Cut each steak across the grain into 1/4-in.-thick slices.'),
('7801', '4', 'In a small bowl, combine 1/3 cup olive oil, the vinegar, and lime juice. In a medium bowl, combine greens, onion, salt, pepper, oranges, avocados, and 2/3 of vinaigrette. toss to coat. Divide salad among 4 plates and arrange tuna slices on top.'),
('7801', '5', 'Serve with remaining vinaigrette on the side.'),
('7801', '6', '*Look for troll- or pole-caught Pacific albacore tuna. it''s more sustainably fished than longline, and the fish have lower mercury levels. U.S. ahi is next best.'),
('7803', '1', 'Preheat an outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil grate.'),
('7803', '2', 'Stir together grapes, capers, shallot, parsley, and olive oil in a bowl. season to taste with salt and pepper, and set aside.'),
('7803', '3', 'Place tuna steaks onto a plate, and brush with lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper to taste.'),
('7803', '4', 'Cook tuna steaks on preheated grill until cooked to desired degree of doneness, 2 to 3 minutes per side for medium-rare.'),
('7803', '5', 'Serve with the grape and caper salsa.'),
('7804', '1', 'Preheat the oven broiler.'),
('7804', '2', 'In a bowl, mix the tuna, mayonnaise, celery, onion, parsley, and vinegar. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7804', '3', 'Place the rye bread slices on a baking sheet, and broil 1 minute in the preheated oven, until lightly toasted.'),
('7804', '4', 'Remove from heat, and spread with the tuna salad.'),
('7804', '5', 'Place 1 cheese slice over the tuna salad on each piece of bread, layer with a tomato slice, and top with remaining cheese slices.'),
('7804', '6', 'Return layered bread to the preheated oven, and broil 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese is melted.'),
('7805', '1', 'Combine the soy sauce, honey, orange juice, sesame oil, garlic, ginger, and cornstarch in a heavy, zip-top plastic bag and add the tuna steaks. Close the bag and marinate the fish for 2 to 4 hours in the refrigerator.'),
('7805', '2', 'Position the oven racks so that the top rack is 6 inches from the top of the oven. Preheat the oven to convection roast at 500F.'),
('7805', '3', 'Place a wire rack on top of a shallow-rimmed roasting pan. Rub the rack with oil.'),
('7805', '4', 'Remove the tuna steaks from the marinade and rub with olive oil.'),
('7805', '5', 'Place on the rack in the roasting pan and roast for 5 to 6 minutes, turning once, until the surface of the tuna is browned but the center is still red.'),
('7805', '6', 'Remove the tuna steaks from the marinade and rub with olive oil.'),
('7805', '7', 'Place on the rack in the roasting pan and roast for 5 to 6 minutes, turning once, until the surface of the tuna is browned but the center is still red.'),
('7805', '8', 'var article'),
('7805', '9', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('7805', '10', 'article'),
('7805', '11', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('7807', '1', 'Save Recipe'),
('7807', '2', 'Print Recipe'),
('7807', '3', 'Mediterranean Tuna Trencher'),
('7807', '4', 'Ingredients4 slices of bread (I like to use a fresh-sliced artisan whole grain or sourdough bread)1  can or jar of tuna packed in olive oil (about 6 oz.)1 tbsp fresh minced parsley1/2 fresh lemon, juiced'),
('7807', '5', 'Salt and pepper'),
('7807', '6', 'Extra virgin olive oil2 tbsp hummus2 tbsp basil pesto2 small Persian cucumbers, thinly sliced1 ripe red tomato, seeded and diced1/4 cup small white cannellini beans (canned), drained and rinsed'),
('7807', '7', 'Arugula (optional, for garnish)Sliced radishes (optional, for garnish)'),
('7807', '8', 'Servings: 4 trenchers'),
('7807', '9', 'Kosher Key: Pareve or dairy (depending on what type of pesto you use)'),
('7811', '1', 'Make the aioli and begin marinating the tuna early in the day. Microwave the lemon and lime in a small bowl to release the essential oils and set aside just long enough to be able to handle. Meanwhile, through the feed tube of a running blender, add 1 at a time, the egg yolks, dry mustard, salt, and white pepper. By this time, the micro-waved lemon and lime should be cool enough to handle. Leaving the blender running, squeeze the juice from half of 1 lemon through the feed opening, then add the oil in a slow stream.'),
('7811', '2', 'Remove to a bowl and refrigerate.'),
('7811', '3', 'Season the tuna steaks with salt and pepper, place them in a nonreactive container and squeeze the rest of the lemon and the lime over them. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.'),
('7811', '4', 'Heat the grill or preheat the broiler in the oven.'),
('7811', '5', 'Brush the marinated tuna with 1 tablespoon or so of olive oil. Cook until browned, until fish flakes with a fork, 3 to 6 minutes per side, and then let rest. Leave grill hot or oven on to toast bread.'),
('7811', '6', 'Brush olive oil (about 1 tablespoon per half) on Italian bread and toast lightly, either on the grill or under broiler.'),
('7811', '7', 'Flake the tuna, place in a bowl with scallions and fennel and fold in the aioli. Spoon tuna mixture onto the toasted Italian bread, drizzle a small amount of balsamic vinegar over, and top with Cheddar.'),
('7811', '8', 'Heat briefly in the oven to melt cheese.'),
('7811', '9', 'Garnish with fresh dill. This is great served with fresh tomato soup, if desired.'),
('7812', '1', 'Preheat oven to 42'),
('7812', '2', 'Stir together cornbread mix and 2/3 cup milk.'),
('7812', '3', 'Pour batter into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan.'),
('7812', '4', 'Bake at 425 for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack 5 minutes or just until warm.'),
('7812', '5', 'Stir together mayonnaise and next 5 ingredients in a large bowl.'),
('7812', '6', 'Crumble cornbread to equal 2 cups. Reserve remaining cornbread for another use. Fold cornbread crumbs and tuna chunks into mayonnaise mixture until well blended. Shape tuna mixture into 8 (3- to 3 1/2-inch) patties.'),
('7812', '7', 'Melt 3 Tbsp. butter with vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('7812', '8', 'Add tuna patties, and cook, in batches, 2 to 3 minutes on each side or until golden brown. drain on paper towels.'),
('7812', '9', 'Serve cakes with Lemon Aoli.'),
('7812', '10', 'Note: For testing purposes only, we used Martha White Buttermilk Cornbread'),
('7812', '11', 'Mix and Star'),
('7812', '12', 'Kist Tuna Creations Herb & Garlic Chunk Light Tuna.'),
('7814', '1', 'In a medium bowl, mix flour with salt and sugar.'),
('7814', '2', 'Add oil and warm water to the flour mixture.'),
('7814', '3', 'Mix everything together using your hands, knead until smooth and pulls away from the side of the bowl.'),
('7814', '4', 'Cut into 8-10 equal pieces. With a rolling pin, roll out each one to a circle about 9 inches in diameter and 1/12 (1.5-2 mm) thick. they need to be really thin almost transparent.Preheat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat. You don''t need to add any oil or butter. Cook the tortilla on both sides until the dough get brown spots all over the tortilla, that will only take few seconds. Must be very careful and work rapidly as they cook really fast. Don''t over cook so the tortilla remain soft and able to be rolled. Once finished, the tortillas are ready to serve.Fill each tortilla with the filling ingredients all the way out to the edges.'),
('7814', '5', 'Roll each tortilla and enjoy as delicious snack or can be cut into 1/2" slices and served as an appetizer.To store let them cool completely and place them in a zipper bag and refrigerate up to 5 days. You can also freeze them in plastic freezer bag but make sure to place parchment paper between tortillas to make sure they do not stick.'),
('7815', '1', 'In a skillet, heat the 2 tablespoons of oil.'),
('7815', '2', 'Add the onion, leeks, thyme and marjoram. Season with salt and pepper. Cook over moderately low heat, stirring, until softened, 10 minutes.'),
('7815', '3', 'Add the sugar, vinegar and carrot and cook until the liquid has evaporated, 5 minutes.'),
('7815', '4', 'Transfer to a bowl and refrigerate until cool.'),
('7815', '5', 'Add the tuna and its oil to the vegetables, breaking the tuna into large flakes.'),
('7815', '6', 'Preheat the broiler.'),
('7815', '7', 'Brush the cut side of the baguettes with oil and toast slightly. Rub the cut sides of the tomato over the baguettes, leaving lots of pulp. Spoon the tuna onto the baguettes, top with the piquillos. serve.'),
('7817', '1', 'Preheat the broiler. In a medium bowl, whisk the 3 tablespoons of olive oil with the red wine vinegar and Dijon mustard until  combined.'),
('7817', '2', 'Add the flaked tuna, chopped artichokes, chopped olives, sliced red onion and shredded basil and toss gently.  Season lightly with salt and pepper.'),
('7817', '3', 'Using a pastry brush, brush the cut sides of the ciabatta lightly with olive oil and broil cut side up on a baking sheet for 2 minutes, until the ciabatta is golden and lightly toasted. shift the baking sheet for even browning. Rub the garlic clove over the toasted ciabatta and mound the tuna salad on top. Cover with the sliced Robiola cheese and broil until the cheese is just melted, about  1 minute.'),
('7817', '4', 'Serve the tuna melts at once.'),
('7820', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.'),
('7820', '2', 'Add the garlic and crushed red pepper and cook over low heat until the garlic is golden, about 3 minutes.'),
('7820', '3', 'Add the tomatoes and their liquid and simmer over moderate heat, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, about 7 minutes.'),
('7820', '4', 'Add the tuna and simmer briefly to heat through. stir gently to keep the tuna in large pieces. Season with salt and black pepper and keep warm.'),
('7820', '5', 'Cook the spaghetti in a large pot of boiling salted water, stirring occasionally, until al dente. Reserve 1/4 cup of the pasta cooking water.'),
('7820', '6', 'Drain the spaghetti and return it to the pot.'),
('7820', '7', 'Add the butter and toss well, then add the tuna sauce, reserved pasta cooking water and basil and toss again. Season with salt and black pepper, transfer to a warmed bowl and serve at once.'),
('7821', '1', 'Cook the penne in boiling salted water until al dente.'),
('7821', '2', 'Drain the pasta, reserving 1/2 cup of the pasta water.'),
('7821', '3', 'Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat the olive oil until shimmering.'),
('7821', '4', 'Add the garlic and cook over moderately high heat until golden, about 2 minutes.'),
('7821', '5', 'Add the drained tuna. cook for 1 minute.'),
('7821', '6', 'Add the wine, capers and 1 tablespoon of the parsley. season with salt and pepper. Cook the sauce until the wine has nearly evaporated, about 2 minutes longer.'),
('7821', '7', 'Add the penne and the reserved pasta water and cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Season with pepper, sprinkle with the remaining 1 tablespoon of parsley and serve.'),
('7822', '1', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan. In a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('7822', '2', 'Add the onions, season with salt and cook over moderately high heat until softened and browned, about 8 minutes.'),
('7822', '3', 'Add the chipotle powder and cook for 30 seconds.'),
('7822', '4', 'Add the oregano and the vinegar and cook for 1 minute.'),
('7822', '5', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('7822', '6', 'Meanwhile, in a bowl, combine the mango, cucumber, serrano, lime juice and cilantro and season the salsa with salt.'),
('7822', '7', 'Oil the grill. Rub the tuna with the remaining 1 tablespoon of olive oil and season with salt. Grill over high heat until lightly charred and pink within, about 3 minutes per side.'),
('7822', '8', 'Transfer to a plate. Grill the tortillas until hot and soft, about 10 seconds. Stack the tortillas and wrap them in foil to keep warm.'),
('7822', '9', 'Thinly slice the tuna and transfer to a platter.'),
('7822', '10', 'Serve with the onions, salsa and tortillas.'),
('7822', '11', 'Let everyone make their own tacos.'),
('7823', '1', 'Spread the tuna, scallions, olives and capers on a plate and freeze for 5 minutes.'),
('7823', '2', 'Transfer to a food processor and pulse until the tuna is finely chopped.'),
('7823', '3', 'Transfer the mixture to a bowl. season with salt and pepper. Form the mixture into four 4-inch patties.'),
('7823', '4', 'Light a grill or preheat a grill pan.'),
('7823', '5', 'Brush the burgers with olive oil and grill over moderately high heat, turning once, until golden and crusty and just cooked through, about 6 minutes.'),
('7823', '6', 'In a bowl, mix the mayonnaise and anchovy paste. spread on the buns. Top with the burgers, tomato and arugula, close and serve.'),
('7824', '1', 'In a medium bowl, mix the mayonnaise with the 1 tablespoon of olive oil from the tuna, the lemon juice, Dijon mustard, celery, roasted garlic, parsley, capers and celery seeds.'),
('7824', '2', 'Mix in the tuna and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7824', '3', 'Spoon the tuna salad onto 4 slices of multigrain bread, top each one with 1 ounce of Gruyre and another slice of bread. Toast the sandwiches in a panini press until theyre golden and the cheese is melted.'),
('7825', '1', 'Heat the olive oil in a large skillet.'),
('7825', '2', 'Add the onion and bay leaf and cook over moderate heat, stirring occasionally until the onion is softened, about 12 minutes.'),
('7825', '3', 'Add the tomatoes and pimentn and cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.'),
('7825', '4', 'Remove from the heat and let cool. Discard the bay leaf.'),
('7825', '5', 'In a bowl, lightly break up the tuna.'),
('7825', '6', 'Add the olives, chopped egg and parsley and stir in the tomato-onion mixture. Season with salt and refrigerate until cool, about 30 minutes.'),
('7825', '7', 'Unfold the puff pastry sheets on a lightly floured work surface. Using a 4 1/2-inch biscuit cutter, cut the pastry into 12 rounds. Using a rolling pin, lightly roll out each round to a 5-inch diameter.'),
('7825', '8', 'Spoon 2 tablespoons of the tuna filling onto 1 side of each pastry round. Fold the pastry over the filling and press the edges to seal decoratively with the tines of a fork.'),
('7825', '9', 'Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper and set 6 empanadas on each sheet. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes, or until chilled.'),
('7825', '10', 'Preheat the oven to 400 and place 2 racks in the center. In a small bowl, whisk the egg with the milk. Lightly brush the empanadas with the egg wash.'),
('7825', '11', 'Bake for 30 minutes, or until the empanadas are deep golden brown.'),
('7825', '12', 'Let cool for 5 minutes before serving.'),
('7826', '1', 'Fit a medium pot with a steamer insert.'),
('7826', '2', 'Add 1 inch of water to the pot and bring it to a boil.'),
('7826', '3', 'Add the tuna and steam until cooked through, about 8 minutes.'),
('7826', '4', 'Let cool. Flake the tuna into a medium bowl. don''t remove the fat. Gently stir in the cilantro, scallions, butter, green peppercorns, lemon juice and cayenne.'),
('7826', '5', 'In a small bowl, beat the cream until stiff. Fold the cream into the tuna and season with salt.'),
('7826', '6', 'Transfer to a crock and serve at room temperature or slightly chilled with crackers.'),
('7827', '1', 'In a medium bowl, mix the tuna with the onion, olive oil, vinegar, basil and crushed red pepper. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7827', '2', 'Heat a panini press or griddle.'),
('7827', '3', 'Spread the cut sides of the rolls with mustard and mayonnaise and top each roll half with a slice of cheese.'),
('7827', '4', 'Spread the tuna salad on the bottoms and cover with the pickles. Close the sandwiches and spread the outsides of the rolls with the butter.'),
('7827', '5', 'Add the sandwiches to the press and cook over moderate heat until the cheese is melted, about 6 minutes.'),
('7827', '6', 'Cut the sandwiches in half and serve.'),
('7830', '1', 'Right in the can, flake the tuna with a fork over a medium bowl, at the same time allowing the tuna to fall into the bowl. Squeeze the lemon over the tuna.'),
('7830', '2', 'Add the remaining ingredients to the bowl and mix well. Taste for seasoning.'),
('7832', '1', 'Stir together first 5 ingredients in a large bowl until blended.'),
('7832', '2', 'Add tuna and next 4 ingredients. toss gently to coat.'),
('7832', '3', 'Serve over greens. Sprinkle with almonds and noodles.'),
('7834', '1', 'Slice the tuna thinly and place in a large shallow serving dish. Sprinkle with salt and cover with the lime juice. Leave to marinate for 40 minutes, turning the fish over once.'),
('7834', '2', 'Lift out the fish (which should now look opaque from being cooked by the lime juice) and put on a plate.'),
('7834', '3', 'Pour the resultant juices into a small bowl.'),
('7834', '4', 'Return the tuna to the dish in a presentable manner. Scatter over the onion and chillies.'),
('7834', '5', 'Arrange the tomatoes, cucumber, and avocado over the top. Sprinkle the cilantro leaves over the surface and finish with the olive oil.'),
('7834', '6', 'Finally, return the collected juices to the dish using a spoon, taking particular care to fully anoint each and every piece of avocado, so preventing any discoloration.'),
('7834', '7', 'Cover and chill for a further 40 minutes or so before serving. Hand round a dish of sour cream at table.'),
('7834', '8', 'var article'),
('7834', '9', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('7834', '10', 'article'),
('7834', '11', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('7835', '1', 'Cook the pasta according to the package directions. Reserve  cup of the cooking water. drain the pasta.Wipe out the pasta pot.'),
('7835', '2', 'Add the oil, garlic, and red pepper and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until fragrant, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('7835', '3', 'Add the pasta, tuna, lemon zest,  teaspoon salt,  teaspoon black pepper, and the reserved pasta water and cook over low heat, tossing, until the sauce is slightly thickened and coats the pasta, 1 to 2 minutes.'),
('7835', '4', 'Add the parsley and toss to combine.'),
('7836', '1', 'Dice tuna into 1/3-inch cubes, discarding fibrous tissue, and place in a glass bowl. Toss tuna gently with olive oil and next 3 ingredients. Cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours.'),
('7836', '2', 'Just before serving, add green onion and next 3 ingredients, and toss. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Arrange in martini glasses, and garnish, if desired.'),
('7836', '3', 'Serve immediately.'),
('7836', '4', 'Chef John Recommends: An aromatic Sauvignon Blanc. Alternative'),
('7836', '5', 'Pours: A Gewrztraminer, Riesling, Viognier, or Muscat to complement the mango.'),
('7838', '1', 'In a small bowl, stir the fish sauce with 2 1/2 tablespoons of the sugar, the water, lemon juice, lime juice, garlic, ginger and the sliced chile.'),
('7838', '2', 'In another small bowl, toss the tomatoes with the soy sauce, vinegar and a pinch of sugar and let stand for 5 minutes.'),
('7838', '3', 'In a medium bowl, gently toss the tuna and watermelon with the dressing. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the salad to 4 plates, allowing as much dressing as possible to drain back into the bowl. Using the slotted spoon, arrange the tomatoes on the plates.'),
('7838', '4', 'Garnish the salads with the tobiko and basil and serve right away.'),
('7841', '1', 'Prepare egg noodles as directed on package. drain and rinse.Preheat oven to 375 degrees'),
('7841', '2', 'Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl'),
('7841', '3', 'Place into a buttered casserole or baking dish and sprinkle evenly with crushed potato chips'),
('7841', '4', 'Bake for 25 minutes or until bubbly'),
('7842', '1', 'In a large bowl, combine the chile oil and soy sauce.'),
('7842', '2', 'Add the tuna and toss well. Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes.'),
('7842', '3', 'Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 35'),
('7842', '4', 'Put the coconut flakes in a pie plate and bake for about 5 minutes, until the coconut flakes are golden brown.'),
('7842', '5', 'In a bowl, whisk the coconut milk with the lime juice, fish sauce and light brown sugar until combined.'),
('7842', '6', 'Mound the cucumber julienne on plates. Top with the tuna and drizzle with the coconut dressing. Sprinkle with the toasted coconut and serve right away with lime wedges.'),
('7843', '1', 'Bring a small pot of salted water to a boil.'),
('7843', '2', 'Add the chopped carrot and celery root and cook over high heat until just tender, 4 to 5 minutes.'),
('7843', '3', 'Drain and let cool under running water. drain again.'),
('7843', '4', 'Transfer the vegetables to a plate lined with paper towels and pat dry.'),
('7843', '5', 'Melt the butter in a large saucepan.'),
('7843', '6', 'Add the onion and cook over moderate heat until softened, about 5 minutes.'),
('7843', '7', 'Add 2/3 cup of the flour and cook, stirring, for 1 minute.'),
('7843', '8', 'Transfer the paste to a large heatproof bowl and slowly whisk in the milk to form a smooth slurry. Return the mixture to the saucepan and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until bubbling and very thick, about 6 minutes.'),
('7843', '9', 'Add the tuna to the white sauce along with the carrots, celery root, salt and pepper. Scrape the croquette mixture into a lightly oiled medium bowl and refrigerate until chilled and firm, at least 4 hours, or preferably overnight.'),
('7843', '10', 'Spread the remaining 1 1/3 cups of flour in a shallow bowl or pie plate.'),
('7843', '11', 'Put the eggs and bread crumbs in 2 shallow bowls or pie plates. Using 2 spoons, shape slightly rounded tablespoons of the croquette mixture into oval patties and drop them, 3 or 4 at a time, into the flour. Turn the croquettes to gently coat them with flour, then dip them in the eggs and coat with bread crumbs. Return the croquettes to the eggs and then the bread crumbs to give them a light second coating.'),
('7843', '12', 'Transfer the finished croquettes to a baking sheet lined with wax paper and continue shaping and coating the remaining croquettes. Loosely cover with wax paper and refrigerate until chilled, at least 30 minutes.'),
('7843', '13', 'Heat 1 inch of vegetable oil in a large deep skillet until shimmering. Working in batches, cook the croquettes over moderately high heat, until golden and crisp, turning frequently, about 2 minutes. lower the heat if they brown too quickly. Using a slotted spoon, transfer the croquettes to paper towels to drain.'),
('7843', '14', 'Serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('7845', '1', 'Drain and rinse the 15-oz can of cannellini beans.'),
('7845', '2', 'Heat the minced garlic in 1 tablespoon of olive oil.'),
('7845', '3', 'Add the cannellini beans and toss with the olive oil.'),
('7845', '4', 'Once the beans are warmed through, place them in a large bowl.'),
('7845', '5', 'Add the 2 cans of drained tuna to this bowl.'),
('7845', '6', 'Halve the heirloom cherry tomatoes and toss them into the large bowl.'),
('7845', '7', 'In a small bowl, whisk together the remaining 5 tablespoons of olive oil, red wine vinegar, Dijon mustard and lemon juice (optional).'),
('7845', '8', 'Pour the vinaigrette over the tuna, beans and tomatoes.'),
('7845', '9', 'Add salt to taste and season generously with freshly ground pepper. Gently toss all ingredients together.'),
('7845', '10', 'Serve at room temperature or chilled with a good piece of bread.'),
('7846', '1', 'The process: wash the basil (cress) and use a salad spinner or clean towel to get the water off. Slice the onions and tomato as thin as you can by hand and set aside. If you have a Kyocera hand slicer (remember mine is named Danton) use it to very thinly slice the radishes or use the mandoline (Robespierre).'),
('7846', '2', 'Assembly: lay out a large sheet of plastic wrap on a board. Slice the loaf in half lengthwise.'),
('7846', '3', 'Put the halves on the cling wrap and scoop out enough of the crumb so that you have two canoes. Give both canoes a generous dose of your best olive oil.'),
('7846', '4', 'Place a good handful of basil leaves on the first canoe.  Top this with the tuna and then the anchovies.'),
('7846', '5', 'Add tomatoes and onion in any order you would like. Finish with olives and radishes, all in a big pile. In the other canoe place the remaining basil. And turn over to cover the sandwich.'),
('7846', '6', 'Wrap it all up in the cling wrap and refrigerate for a couple of hours. Great for those days when you dont want to turn on the oven. Like today for example. Put on your espadrilles.'),
('7846', '7', '*If I ever hear any of you use the term EVOO you will be permanently off the recipe list. Why? Because even though Rachael Ray has her own labled brand she doesnt even know what it Extra Virgin means. And Im flat out serious. The world must be saved from this evil woman.'),
('7846', '8', 'Lets get started! Myself, I like to use a Spanish style oil made from arbequina olives. There are now several Californial brands.'),
('7847', '1', 'Combine the scallions, ginger, egg and tuna in a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Form the mixture into 6 patties (they will be quite loose), set on a plate and cover with plastic wrap.'),
('7847', '2', 'Put the burgers in the fridge for at least 15 minutes to firm up a little.'),
('7847', '3', 'Meanwhile, slice the cucumber into wide ribbons using a peeler and make the wasabi ginger mayonnaise: stir together the mayonnaise, wasabi and pickled ginger.'),
('7847', '4', 'Add a little water if needed to thin the mayo. Cover and set aside.'),
('7847', '5', 'Set a large, nonstick pan over medium-high heat and add 1 tablespoon oil. When the oil is hot, add the burgers to the pan in batches. Cook until golden brown on the bottom, about three minutes. Flip and cook for another few minutes, until just cooked through (you can stop the burgers at medium rare, but I like them closer to medium/medium-well). Keep in a warm place while you cook the rest of the burgers.'),
('7847', '6', 'Toast the buns and serve the burgers on top, with a generous dollop of the wasabi mayonnaise, a handful of sprouts and a few ribbons of cucumber.'),
('7850', '1', 'Cook egg noodles until al dente according to package directions.'),
('7850', '2', 'Drain, rinse with cold water, and drain again.'),
('7850', '3', 'Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat.'),
('7850', '4', 'Add leeks and cook, covered, 7 minutes or until tender but not browned.'),
('7850', '5', 'Whisk in flour. cook 1 minute.'),
('7850', '6', 'Pour in milk. bring mixture to a boil over medium-high heat, whisking frequently. Reduce heat to medium-low, and simmer 3 minutes or until sauce is smooth and thickened.'),
('7850', '7', 'Remove from heat, and whisk in cheese and next 3 ingredients. Fold in tuna and egg noodles.'),
('7850', '8', 'Pour into a greased 3-quart baking dish.'),
('7850', '9', 'Combine olive oil, garlic, and panko. sprinkle over casserole.'),
('7850', '10', 'Bake at 375 for 30 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.'),
('7850', '11', 'Let stand 5 minutes before serving.'),
('7851', '1', 'Place the tuna in a saucepan, just large enough to hold it (see the slideshow). Wedge the thyme and garlic around the sides.'),
('7851', '2', 'Pour in the olive oil, and life the tuna so some oil spreads beneath it. You want the tuna to be 1/2 to 2/3 covered. Season with salt.'),
('7851', '3', 'Set the pan over medium low heat (if your stove is BTU-rific, you may need to keep it at low). Gently poach the tuna, spooning warm oil over the top as it goes and turning the tuna once. You want to cook it until it''s still pink inside but cooked through.'),
('7851', '4', 'Remove to a cutting board. Save the delicious oil.'),
('7851', '5', 'Slice the potatoes, and halve the green beans (if they''re large. keep them whole if small). Divide the potatoes, green beans and cranberry beans among 4 plates. Use your fingers to pull the tuna into bite-size pieces and arrange atop the vegetables. Spoon the reserved poaching oil over the salad. Sprinkle a teaspoon of vinegar over each salad. Season with salt and coarsely ground black pepper.'),
('7851', '6', 'Note: If using dried cranberry beans, soak the beans over night.'),
('7851', '7', 'Drain. Cover with cold water, bring to a boil and cook until just tender, 60 to 90 minutes.'),
('7852', '1', 'Whisk the lemon juice, vinegar, and mustard together in a bowl.'),
('7852', '2', 'Add the oils in a slow stream, whisking vigorously, to form a light emulsion. Season to taste with salt and pepper, and set aside.'),
('7852', '3', 'Bring a pot of water to a rolling boil.'),
('7852', '4', 'Cut the stem core out of the top of the tomatoes and cut an X in the bottom. Plunge the tomatoes into the boiling water for 15-20 seconds, then rinse under cold water. The peel can now be removed easily. Slice the tomatoes in half crosswise and remove the seeds and pulp.'),
('7852', '5', 'Put the tomatoes, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper to taste, and the vinaigrette into a food processor or blender and process until well blended. Thin with a little vinegar if necessary.'),
('7852', '6', 'Allow the tuna fillets to stand at room temperature for 15 minutes. Season all sides with salt and pepper.'),
('7852', '7', 'Heat the 3 tablespoons of olive oil in a large, heavy skillet until almost smoking.'),
('7852', '8', 'Place 4 tuna blocks at a time in the pan and cook over high heat for about 20 seconds per side, until all sides are lightly browned. Repeat until all of the tuna is cooked, adding more olive oil if necessary.'),
('7852', '9', 'Toss the arugula or spring mix with enough vinaigrette to coat and arrange in the center of the plate.'),
('7852', '10', 'Place tuna around the salad and drizzle with more of the vinaigrette.'),
('7852', '11', 'var article'),
('7852', '12', 'Type_27_data = {}.'),
('7852', '13', 'article'),
('7852', '14', 'Type_27_data.init_step_by_step_images = 0.'),
('7854', '1', 'Heat the oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('7854', '2', 'Add the bell pepper, onion and garlic. cook and stir until limp. Reduce the heat to medium, and stir in the seasoned salt, rosemary and ketchup. Simmer, stirring constantly, until slightly brown.'),
('7854', '3', 'Mix in the tuna, and cook for about 5 more minutes to blend the flavors before serving.'),
('7855', '1', 'In a saucepan, saute green pepper in butter until tender.'),
('7855', '2', 'Stir in flour, sugar, salt and pepper until blended. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly. Stir in tomatoes. Bring to a boil. cook and stir for 2 minutes.'),
('7855', '3', 'Add tuna and Creole seasoning. heat through.'),
('7856', '1', 'In a small skillet, toast the pine nuts over moderate heat until lightly browned, about 2 minutes.'),
('7856', '2', 'Transfer to a medium bowl.'),
('7856', '3', 'Add the tuna, wine and lemon zest, 1/2 cup of the cherry tomatoes and 2 tablespoons each of the olive oil and fennel fronds. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.'),
('7856', '4', 'Heat the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a large, deep skillet.'),
('7856', '5', 'Add the crushed red pepper and the remaining cherry tomatoes and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until the sauce is flavorful, about 10 minutes.'),
('7856', '6', 'Meanwhile, cook the linguine in boiling salted water until al dente. Reserve 1/4 cup of the pasta cooking water, then drain the linguine.'),
('7856', '7', 'Add the tuna mixture and the remaining 2 tablespoons of fennel fronds to the skillet and cook over low heat, stirring just until the tuna starts to whiten, about 1 1/2 minutes.'),
('7856', '8', 'Remove the skillet from the heat.'),
('7856', '9', 'Add the linguine and the reserved pasta cooking water and toss well. Season with salt and pepper and serve at once.'),
('7860', '1', 'Preheat grill pan to high or preheat grill or charcoal. Coat tuna in balsamic and season with rosemary, salt and pepper.'),
('7860', '2', 'Drizzle fish with oil, coating lightly on both sides, about 2 tablespoons oil, total.'),
('7860', '3', 'Preheat a medium nonstick skillet over medium high heat.'),
('7860', '4', 'Add 2 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, 2 turns of the pan in a slow stream.'),
('7860', '5', 'Add garlic, onion and saute 2 or 3 minutes. Dice the zucchini and squash while the onion begins to soften.'),
('7860', '6', 'Add the zucchini and squash to the pan and turn to coat and combine with garlic and onion.'),
('7860', '7', 'Slice eggplant into strips and dice, then add to the pan. Turn to combine all of the vegetables.'),
('7860', '8', 'Add thyme, salt and pepper to season the mixture. Cook over medium high heat, stirring frequently, 10 minutes, until vegetables are just fork tender.'),
('7860', '9', 'Grill tuna 2 to 3 minutes on each side for rare, up to 6 minutes on each side for well done.'),
('7860', '10', 'When tuna is done and vegetables are fork tender, stir chopped tomatoes into eggplant and zucchini mixture and remove vegetables from heat.'),
('7860', '11', 'Serve wedges of vegetable antipasto, above recipe, along side tuna steaks topped with vegetable salsa. Extra antipasto slices and vegetables should be passed at the table.'),
('7860', '12', 'A nice Sicilian rose, chilled, makes a fine beverage companion.'),
('7860', '13', '1 loaf crusty bread, 9 to 12 inches in length'),
('7860', '14', '1/4 cup sun-dried tomatoes in olive oil, drained, chopped -- 1/2 a small jar'),
('7860', '15', '1/4 cup black pitted calamata or oil cured olives, your preference, chopped'),
('7860', '16', '1/2 cup prepared pesto sauce'),
('7860', '17', '1/4 pound deli sliced provolone'),
('7860', '18', '1 jar, 16 to 18 roasted red peppers, drained'),
('7860', '19', '1 (15-ounce) can quartered artichoke hearts in water, drained'),
('7860', '20', '1 cup giardiniera, pickled vegetables (hot pickled peppers, cauliflower, carrots available on the Italian foods aisle of market or in bulk bins near deli section with bulk olives)'),
('7860', '21', 'Coarse salt and black pepper'),
('7860', '22', 'Extra-virgin olive oil, for drizzling'),
('7860', '23', 'Cut the top off a loaf of crusty bread. Hollow out the inside of the bread.'),
('7860', '24', 'Mix parsley, chopped sun-dried tomatoes, chopped olives and store bought or homemade pesto sauce.'),
('7860', '25', 'Spread the mixture evenly across the bottom of the hollowed out bread. Layer the cheese into the loaf. Layer the roasted red peppers on top of the cheese. Coarsely chop the drained artichoke hearts and add them in a layer over the red peppers. Sprinkle in the chopped hot pickled vegetables and drizzle some extra-virgin olive oil on top. Replace the top, cut the stuffed loaf into pieces and serve.'),
('7863', '1', 'In a saucepan, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil.'),
('7863', '2', 'Add the carrot, onion and garlic and cook over moderate heat, stirring, until slightly softened, 5 minutes.'),
('7863', '3', 'Add the wheat berries, chicken broth and water and season with salt. Bring to a boil and cook over moderately high heat until the wheat berries are tender, 30 minutes.'),
('7863', '4', 'Drain well and return the wheat berries and vegetables to the saucepan. Season with salt and pepper and let cool for 10 minutes.'),
('7863', '5', 'Stir the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil and the lemon juice into the wheat berries. Fold in the tuna, olives, arugula and fennel. Season with salt and pepper and serve warm or at room temperature.'),
('7864', '1', 'In a bowl, mix the shallot, vinegar, maple syrup, capers and a pinch of salt and pepper. let stand for 15 minutes.'),
('7864', '2', 'Whisk in the oil.'),
('7864', '3', 'Meanwhile, place the tuna between sheets of plastic wrap and pound until the steaks are 1/4 inch thick. Rub with oil and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7864', '4', 'Preheat a griddle.'),
('7864', '5', 'Add the tuna and cook on one side only until lightly seared, 1 minute.'),
('7864', '6', 'Transfer to plates, browned side up.'),
('7864', '7', 'Add the parsley, pomegranate seeds and fennel to the dressing and season with hot sauce. Toss gently, mound the salad over the tuna and serve right away.'),
('7865', '1', 'In a saucepan, combine the orange and lemon juices and boil over high heat until reduced to 1/3 cup, 7 minutes.'),
('7865', '2', 'Transfer to a bowl. let cool. Stir in the vinegar, soy, jalapeo and ginger.'),
('7865', '3', 'Whisk in the olive oil. season with salt and pepper.'),
('7865', '4', 'In a small skillet, toast the sesame seeds over moderately high heat, shaking the pan until golden, 2 to 3 minutes.'),
('7865', '5', 'Cut the tuna into 4 equal pieces.'),
('7865', '6', 'Place 1 piece of tuna between 2 sheets of plastic and pound to a 1/8-inch thickness.'),
('7865', '7', 'Remove the top sheet of plastic and invert the tuna onto a plate. Repeat with the remaining tuna.'),
('7865', '8', 'Stir the dressing and spoon it over the tuna.'),
('7865', '9', 'Garnish with the radishes and sesame seeds and serve.'),
('7866', '1', 'Cook the spaghetti in a large pot of boiling salted water until al dente.'),
('7866', '2', 'Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat 1/4 cup of the olive oil until shimmering.'),
('7866', '3', 'Add the garlic and cook over moderate heat until fragrant, about 30 seconds.'),
('7866', '4', 'Add the pancetta and crushed red pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until the pancetta is golden and crisp, about 5 minutes.'),
('7866', '5', 'Add the spinach and tuna, breaking up the tuna with a spoon.'),
('7866', '6', 'Add the wine and cook until nearly evaporated, about 1 minute.'),
('7866', '7', 'Drain the spaghetti, reserving 1/2 cup of the cooking liquid.'),
('7866', '8', 'Add the pasta and reserved cooking liquid to the skillet and cook over moderate heat, tossing, until the liquid is nearly absorbed, about 1 minute.'),
('7866', '9', 'Drizzle with the remaining 2 tablespoons of olive oil, season with salt and serve immediately.'),
('7867', '1', 'In a large, shallow dish, combine the cider and 2 tablespoons of the olive oil.'),
('7867', '2', 'Add the tuna steaks and turn to coat.'),
('7867', '3', 'Let stand for 15 minutes, turning once.'),
('7867', '4', 'Meanwhile, light a grill. In a medium bowl, stir the crme frache with the chipotles, garlic, chopped basil and apple and season with salt and pepper.'),
('7867', '5', 'Season the tuna with salt and pepper. Grill over a hot fire, turning once, until lightly charred on the outside and rare inside, about 6 minutes.'),
('7867', '6', 'Transfer to a platter.'),
('7867', '7', 'Brush the ciabatta slices on both sides with olive oil and grill over a hot fire until toasted on both sides.'),
('7867', '8', 'Cut the tuna into 1/3-inch-thick slices and arrange the slices on the toasts. Top each bruschetta with a dollop of chipotle crme frache and a basil leaf and serve.'),
('7868', '1', 'In a small bowl, whisk the lemon juice with the mustard, then slowly whisk in the olive oil. Stir in the chives and season the lemon-mustard vinaigrette with salt and pepper.'),
('7868', '2', 'In a large bowl, gently toss the drained tuna with the sliced celery, butter beans and capers.'),
('7868', '3', 'Add the lemon-mustard vinaigrette and toss to coat the salad. Season the salad with salt and pepper and serve at once.'),
('7869', '1', 'In a food processor, combine 4 tablespoons of the butter with the tuna and red pepper and process to a coarse puree. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('7869', '2', 'In a small skillet, melt the remaining 1 tablespoon of butter.'),
('7869', '3', 'Add the pine nuts and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until golden brown, about 3 minutes.'),
('7869', '4', 'Spread about 2 teaspoons of tuna mousse on each toast and transfer to a platter.'),
('7869', '5', 'Garnish with the toasted pine nuts and serve.'),
('7870', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('7870', '2', 'Rinse and pat tuna steaks dry.'),
('7870', '3', 'Place zest on top of cutting board. Pile rosemary and parsley leaves on top of zest. Pile garlic and some coarse salt and black pepper or grill seasoning on top of herbs. Finely chop the garlic, herbs, and spices.'),
('7870', '4', 'Drizzle the olive oil over the tuna steaks just enough to coat each side. Rub herb and garlic mixture into fish, coating pieces evenly on each side.'),
('7870', '5', 'Let stand 10 minutes.'),
('7870', '6', 'Grill tuna steaks 6 minutes on each side or 4 minutes on each side, if you prefer pink tuna at the center. Cook steaks over: high setting on indoor electric grill, medium high heat on outdoor gas grill or, 6 inches from hot, prepared charcoal.'),
('7870', '7', 'Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl or large food storage plastic bag. Coat mushroom caps evenly in marinade.'),
('7870', '8', 'Place mushroom caps on the grill cap-side-up and season with grill seasoning or salt and pepper. If you are using an indoor tabletop electric grill, preheat to 400 degrees F or "high" setting. If you are using an outdoor gas grill, preheat to medium high. for a charcoal grill, prepare coals and cook mushrooms 6 inches from hot coals. Mushrooms will cook 4 to 6 minutes on each side. Cook mushrooms covered or under tin foil tent and turn occasionally.'),
('7870', '9', 'Combine tomatoes, rosemary, and smoked mozzarella.'),
('7870', '10', 'Drizzle with oil and toss.'),
('7870', '11', 'Fill mushroom caps with tomato mixture and top with sliced mozzarella. The mushrooms will look like small pizzas.'),
('7870', '12', 'Place caps in oven at 425 degrees F until cheese melts or you can close grill lid or replace tin foil tent over mushroom caps to melt cheese, it will take 1 to 3 minutes.'),
('7870', '13', 'Serve as-is or, place stuffed caps on garlic toast or sliced crusty bread to catch the juices.'),
('7885', '1', 'Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl.'),
('7885', '2', 'Combine basil and oil. stir with a whisk.'),
('7885', '3', 'Cut bread in half horizontally. Hollow out top and bottom halves of bread, leaving a 1-inch-thick shell. reserve torn bread for another use. Rub cut sides of garlic clove over cut sides of bread. discard garlic.'),
('7885', '4', 'Drizzle basil mixture evenly over cut sides of bread. Spoon tuna mixture on bottom half of baguette. Arrange tomato slices over tuna mixture. Cover with top half of baguette. Wrap filled baguette in plastic wrap, and let stand for 20 minutes.'),
('7885', '5', 'Cut filled baguette into 4 (3-inch) equal portions.'),
('7891', '1', 'Rub and season the ahi tuna steak with the Shichimi Togarashi, for 15 minutes.'),
('7891', '2', 'Heat up a pan on medium heat and add some olive oil to coat the pan. Pan-sear each side of the ahi tuna steak for about 30 seconds or as soon as the surface turns opaque. Dish out and let cool in the fridge.Prepare the Dressing by mixing all the ingredients together.To serve, toss the salad with the dressing and divide the salad into individual serving bowls. Slice the ahi tuna into pieces and lay them on the salad.'),
('7891', '3', 'Add some Tobikko, shredded roasted seaweed, and sesame as toppings and serve immediately.'),
('7894', '1', 'In a bowl combine celery, tomatoes, chick peas, onions, parsley and olives. Flake tuna and add to the salad. Dress salad with juice of 2 lemons and about 1/3 cup olive oil. Season the salad with salt and pepper and toss.'),
('7898', '1', 'Add the tuna in a food processor and pulse to grind.'),
('7898', '2', 'Put the tuna in bowl and stir in the chives, tamari, garlic, and black pepper, to taste.'),
('7898', '3', 'Add the panko crumbs and sesame seeds to a shallow dish. Form the tuna mixture into 8 small patties and roll in the bread crumbs.');